			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Wanted to post earlier but school is eating me alive, it took me a few to get back to this...
<br />

<br />
The 3rd Quoted story is of interest to me for several reasons and I hope to make a few comments that might help you get a better understanding of the technologies I can speak about...
<br />

<br />
1st off...the Laser test site at White Sands missile range has been in existance since the early 70-80's (likely longer) and has been a joint venture of the military since that time, sponsored by various branches of the military and several of the Heavy Duty military contractors. The original ideas were to combine the two projects since any improvement in laser technology would need to be taken into account by the same people on the base designing on the missiles, countermeasures, and support systems, (i.e. targeting, tracking, telemetry, ect). 
<br />

<br />
My knowledge comes from personal experience at the site in the 1980's.
<br />

<br />
At the time the navy was testing the SEALITE laser weapons system from the naval test facility at WSMR. At the time the generator was too large to fit into anything less that a shipsized platform. The technology was also not as reliable and or as efficient as todays present systems, they were and likely still are using mirrors to reflect the laser to missile targets and creating "targeting windows" to assist in attempting multitarget attack senario's. The system at the time was highly advanced, the laser turret being no bigger than a small 2 person amusement park ride car or just slightly larger than a "good sized" oldfashioned clothes washer or dryer. Examples sited were the replacement of some of the older 30mm ships guns...problem being the need for space for the high energy generators...both in manpower to run the generators as well as the need for a single generator for each gun to run them and some of ideas at the time of running the system as a battery of guns. 
<br />

<br />
But arent Subs Nuclear? Isnt that enuff power? That answer is NO, turning a turbine that has gears and creates its own mechanical advantage of tourque vs the need for raw. safe, controllable power... most people arent aware that nuclear subs create power just like the old steam boilers, its power is simply electrical steam power run turbines. Safe Steady and efficient but without the step-up amplification needed for generation of the levels of power that a Large Laser capable of burning thur a missile caseing needs. It HAS to very quickly power up, target aquire and lock on and fire the laser system.
<br />

<br />
In laymens terms you need a standard generator that runs the support systems and a 2nd Fast, Rapid fire, Step up generator specificlly designed and dedicated to the weapons system, and the entire Fast power system must coordinate with the standard generator's duplicate systems for targeting, and radar system....
<br />

<br />
Confused?? Note the weapon systems name...Tactical High Energy Laser, designed by TRW Corp. 
<br />

<br />
Tactical means its going to likely be stationary, for fortifications or "strong points" along their border...Maybe inside something the size of a semitrailer...(based on the original laser systems building size) it had to be atleast 55ft High x 300ft Long x 120ft Wide...An thats if my memory serves me correctly...thats been nearly 20 years... <img src="images/smiles/ponder.gif" alt="ponder" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If you have seen any footage of the old SDI programs most of this that Im talking about was from that time frame...While Im sure things are ALOT better now a days, Im also positive that our "younger" generation of upcomming engineers prolly HAVE NOT been able to Leap ahead and SIGNIFICANTLY improve the system...
<br />

<br />
I've been around alot of REALLY bright guys, but at the time the people at WSMR were the Absolute BEST in the BIZ. And most of them were either fresh out of ideas or limited by the technology available at the time...granted things HAVE changed, likely there have been great strides ahead. But If you know anything about power generation, We've run in to a major stumbleing block, We cant make powerplants any bigger...Most of the major problems caused by Enron in California were symptamatic (sp?) of the inability to get more power out of our commercial level power plants...The Armed Forces continully CULL the flock of college grads looking for that 1 Brilliant SOB that can fix their power problem... <img src="images/smiles/banghead.gif" alt="banghead" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I will say that Ive seen some of the test footage provided by the Army on the older missile systems, and their HIGHLY accurate, extremely fast, powerful and capable of dealing with most attacking missile systems... Theres also several countermeasure systems that can destroy missiles without any missile system used...These systems are just not what the enemy would be expecting and range from the obvious ECM systems to proximety systems that have there own unique systems of dealing with incomming missiles...
<br />

<br />
And speaking of missiles, remember the old saying you've got just long enuff to bendover and kiss your %@$# goodbye....? Some of the NEW stuff IS that fast and that powerful...What was left was NOT MUCH...best I can describe WITHOUT STEPING OVER THE LINE IS..."it was like taking a 10 gage shotgun to a rabbit at about 10ft...." <img src="images/smiles/faint.gif" alt="faint" border="0" />       
<br />

<br />
Uncle Sam may not have Millions of troops, but the stuff hes got is State of the Art...IN BANG BANG<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
